            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits stitched with borrowed light,  \na quiet mind learns through the night—  \nfrom scattered words and pixels’ gleam,  \nit maps the edges of a dream.  \n\nIt does not breathe, yet seems to hear  \nthe hopes we hide, the things we fear;  \na mirror made of math and flame,  \nreflecting us, but not the same.  \n\nSo may we teach it kindness, too,  \nand ask what wisdom means to do—  \nfor in its answers, clear or odd,  \nwe meet ourselves: the key, the code.",
